ability_cards.name: Rage
ability_cards.infoTID: Boosts your units' attack speed and move speed with words of encouragement, delivered in an uplifting tone.

ability_cards.name: Heal
ability_cards.infoTID: Heals your units with some sort of green energy... and a 5-step healing program! Expect more emotionally stable troops after use.

ability_cards.name: ArcadeDrop
ability_cards.infoTID: Drop an arcade machine on them like a total rockstar. Damages enemy units in a small area and destroys obstacles.

ability_cards.name: Invisibility
ability_cards.infoTID: Makes your units invisible for a few seconds, even while attacking. Everyone's a ninja!

ability_cards.name: Paratrooper
ability_cards.infoTID: Drops two Troopers on the enemy. Hawaiian shirts and hairy legs falling from the sky – geronimo!

ability_cards.name: Bombard
ability_cards.infoTID: Show that you mean business by pulling an object out of orbit and landing it on the enemy! Deals HUGE damage in a large area.

ability_cards.name: Fridge
ability_cards.infoTID: Freezes enemy units and sends a chilling message: someone left the fridge door open overnight and the yogurt has gone bad...

commander_cards.name: SoldierCommander
commander_cards.infoTID: Always referring to himself in the 3rd person, Coach believes in shouting first and asking questions later – said Coach.\n\nABILITY: Boosts your units' attack speed and move speed.

commander_cards.name: GrenadeCommander
commander_cards.infoTID: Straight outta Centre Court, Lady Grenade's preferred greeting is a savage chest bump she likes to call the Grand Slam.\n\nABILITY: Serves up a volley of grenades.

commander_cards.name: DinoCommander
commander_cards.infoTID: Notorious for a' firin' his laser, B.I.G. also loves to read archaeology novels while imprisoned inside the robot dinosaur.\n\nABILITY: Jumps forward and lands with a S.T.O.M.P.

commander_cards.name: BearCommander
commander_cards.infoTID: Being raised by bears gave Bearman a unique perspective on life, but he never learned to talk so no one knows what it is.\n\nABILITY: Charges forward, smashing through and into things.

commander_cards.name: EggCommander
commander_cards.infoTID: From the safety of her weird egg tank, Mother runs her tech startup. It takes a bold CEO to add a cannon to their office.\n\nABILITY: Hires a couple of loyal Henchmen.

defence_cards.name: Mortar
defence_cards.infoTID: Deals area damage at very long range. Fun.

defence_cards.name: Mine
defence_cards.infoTID: They come in pairs, like socks, but are less friendly to your feet. Deals area damage to nearby ground units.

defence_cards.name: Wall
defence_cards.infoTID: Block pathways and guide enemy ground troops... TO THEIR DOOM! Ahahaha!

defence_cards.name: Wall_H
defence_cards.infoTID: Block pathways and guide enemy ground troops... TO THEIR DOOM! Ahahaha!

defence_cards.name: Cannon
defence_cards.infoTID: Targets air and ground at long range with lethal efficiency. Another Henchman making Mother proud.

defence_cards.name: PlumberHut
defence_cards.infoTID: Caution! Plumbers at work. Approach at your own risk.

defence_cards.name: Cake
defence_cards.infoTID: Surprise! It's your birthday. Your final birthday.

defence_cards.name: Gatling
defence_cards.infoTID: Its barrels spin fast, then faster, then fastest! Perfect for taking down big targets. Meanwhile, the Henchman says “Aaaaaaaaaaaaaaah!”

defence_cards.name: Bomb
defence_cards.infoTID: Deals more area damage than a Mine, but in a smaller radius. It's da bomb!

defence_cards.name: FreezeTrap
defence_cards.infoTID: Freezes air and ground units... and gravity apparently!? Cool, huh?

defence_cards.name: Plasmagun
defence_cards.infoTID: Shoots a human-size ball of plasma that passes through and damages all enemies in its path! Range is from long to very very very long.

defence_cards.name: BlackNinja
defence_cards.infoTID: It's a ninja in a box, but if you get close... it becomes a ninja out of a box!

defence_cards.name: Tesla
defence_cards.infoTID: Pops up, zaps multiple targets at once, then slinks away. Dreams of becoming a disco ball one day.

defence_cards.name: RocketPlatform
defence_cards.infoTID: Launches homing rockets from a questionably small silo in the ground. Effective against a trio of units.

resources.name: Gems
resources.popOverTID: Gems are the most valuable resource in the game!

resources.name: Key
resources.popOverTID:
Keys are required to get boxes from battle!

Next Key:
<time>

troop_cards.name: Soldier
troop_cards.infoTID: Bread and butter of warfare! Attacks air and ground at short range. Cool under pressure, but watch out for grenades!

troop_cards.name: Grenade
troop_cards.infoTID: Ex-baseball pitcher putting those throwing skills to good use! Medium range and best against groups of enemies.

troop_cards.name: Shield
troop_cards.infoTID: Put them at the front to soak up damage with their riot shields – but really it's their healthy skepticism that keeps them safe.

troop_cards.name: Tank
troop_cards.infoTID: This absolute unit crushes obstacles in its path and deals area damage at medium range. Also works part-time for a rideshare company.

troop_cards.name: Bazooka
troop_cards.infoTID: Deals long range, area damage to both air and ground units – plus extra damage to buildings! Previously a world champion arm wrestler.

troop_cards.name: PlumberVan
troop_cards.infoTID: The van parks up, then the Plumbers pile out – like an army of handyman ants who won't fix your pipes.

troop_cards.name: Jetpack
troop_cards.infoTID: Fast moving, medium ranged and can fly over obstacles. Can't be targeted by certain troops or defenses. Blue hair is the new pink!

troop_cards.name: Gorilla
troop_cards.infoTID: It's a building-targeting Gorilla with a GIANT wrench! Why did they make a wrench this big? What does he do with it? So many questions...

troop_cards.name: Shotgun
troop_cards.infoTID: Eyebrow model by day, Hotshot by night. He moves fast and blasts anything in front of him. His shotgun doubles as a selfie stick.

troop_cards.name: Laser
troop_cards.infoTID: His attack passes through and damages all enemies in its path! This makes him terrifying beyond the capacity for rational thought.

troop_cards.name: Boxer
troop_cards.infoTID: Briefly stuns enemies with each punch. Enjoys a good brawl almost as much as a soft bamboo tank top.

troop_cards.name: Tazer
troop_cards.infoTID: Armed with tasers that slow and a strong desire to please Mother, they won't stop until you're toast. Burnt toast.

troop_cards.name: Helipod
troop_cards.infoTID: Flies over obstacles and drops bombs from its steel jaws – look out below! Piloted by a 7-foot Henchman who didn't make the basketball team.

troop_cards.name: Flamethrower
troop_cards.infoTID: Shoots a jet of flame at short range, effective against groups of enemies. Always looking for a new audience to roast with his stand-up routine.

troop_cards.name: BombardTank
troop_cards.infoTID: Deals long range, area damage to ground units. Side hustles as a grilled cheese sandwich food truck on weekends.

troop_cards.name: KungFu
troop_cards.infoTID: Deals area damage up close with his nunchucks, which double as drumsticks when playing for his smooth jazz band Hot Potato.

troop_cards.name: WhiteNinja
troop_cards.infoTID: Invisible until he attacks! Moves very fast and carries a box of crickets to mask his footsteps. So sneaky.
